      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUVTOBEUPTOME (5) was very consistent when tackling the top juveniles last season, placing in both the Vicbred and Breeders Crown finals at this circuit and distance. Hasn't raced since December but has recorded a win and a placing in two fresh attempts and two trial wins suggest he has come back in good order. MOST EXCITING (6) is progressing nicely having won both starts this time in, leading to cruise home by 9m at this circuit and distance a fortnight ago. Draws wider so may not enjoy the same favours but should have the fitness edge on the top pick. LE CARDINAL (7) was held up when beaten only 2.6m here last week. Draws wide but had looked good in overcoming back row draws to win his first two outings of this campaign. SOLS ME NAME (3) tackles some handy rivals here but has done a good job to win both starts since a spell and draws well.",
